{
"@type":"Question",
"name":"What is Full Stack Web Development?",
"acceptedAnswer":{
"@type":"Answer",
"text":"Full Stack Web Development involves building both front-end and back-end components of web applications including user interfaces, APIs, databases and deployment."
}
},
{
"@type":"Question",
"name":"Is this Full Stack Developer course suitable for beginners?",
"acceptedAnswer":{
"@type":"Answer",
"text":"Yes. The course is designed for beginners, career switchers, students and professionals with no prior programming experience."
}
},
{
"@type":"Question",
"name":"What technologies are covered in this Full Stack Web Development course?",
"acceptedAnswer":{
"@type":"Answer",
"text":"Students learn HTML, CSS, JavaScript, React, Node.js, Express, SQL databases, REST APIs, Git, GitHub and deployment workflows."
}
},
{
"@type":"Question",
"name":"How long is the Full Stack Web Development training?",
"acceptedAnswer":{
"@type":"Answer",
"text":"The programme consists of 6 days and 48 hours of instructor-led training with practical project labs."
}
},
{
"@type":"Question",
"name":"Will I build real-world projects during the course?",
"acceptedAnswer":{
"@type":"Answer",
"text":"Yes. Students complete portfolio projects, deploy applications publicly and participate in project-based learning activities."
}
}
